### 2025-11-24 - Session 6: Bug Fix - Sidebar Drag-Drop Reload Issue
**Time:** ~30 minutes
**Status:** 🔄 In Progress

**Problem:**
User reported that dragging sidebar items sometimes causes page to reload (white flash) when drag operation completes.

**Root Cause:**
When drag-drop ends and user releases mouse, the mouseup event propagates to the Link component, triggering navigation to the same route. React Router navigates even to the same page, causing visible page reload.

**Solution:**
- Added `justDragged` state flag to track when drag operation just completed
- Modified `handleDragEnd` to set `justDragged: true` and reset after 100ms
- Updated `SortableNavItem` to prevent Link navigation if `justDragged` is true
- Added onClick handler to Link: `if (justDragged) e.preventDefault()`

**Files Modified:**
- src/components/Sidebar.tsx (lines 149, 170-186, 39, 42, 60-66, 357)

**Changes:**
- Added state: `const [justDragged, setJustDragged] = useState(false);`
- Updated handleDragEnd: Sets justDragged flag, resets after 100ms timeout
- Updated SortableNavItemProps interface: Added `justDragged: boolean`
- Updated SortableNavItem: Accepts justDragged prop, prevents Link onClick
- Updated parent render: Passes `justDragged={justDragged}` to component

**Testing:**
- ✅ TypeScript type-check passed
- ⏳ Manual testing needed: Drag sidebar items, verify no reload flash

**Commit:** "fix: Prevent page reload when dragging sidebar navigation items"
